@startuml
scale 1400 width
title VBoxManage clipboard serve - lazy host data request path
hide empty description
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 96

[*] --> Setup : serve starts
Setup : Get IClipboard and IHostClipboard
Setup : Register event listener
Setup --> ServeLoop
Setup --> Failed : setup error

state ServeLoop {
  [*] --> Waiting
  Waiting : Common wait state
  Waiting : waits for event, timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Stopping : timeout or signal
  Waiting --> Dispatch : event received

  Dispatch : Decode VBoxEventType
  Dispatch --> DataRequestedEvent : DataRequested
  Dispatch --> OtherEvent : SourceChanged, FormatChanged,\nDataChanged, Transfer, Error or ModeChanged

  DataRequestedEvent : Extract requestId, action, source and format
  DataRequestedEvent --> ReadGuestData : requestId != 0\naction == Copy\nsource == Guest
  DataRequestedEvent --> Continue : malformed or not Guest/Copy

  ReadGuestData : IClipboard::ReadDataRaw(action, mime)
  ReadGuestData --> ValidateReadData : read succeeded
  ReadGuestData --> Continue : warning only

  ValidateReadData : Require source == Guest
  ValidateReadData : Require MIME equivalent to requested format
  ValidateReadData : Require non-empty payload
  ValidateReadData --> ProvideGuestData : valid guest data
  ValidateReadData --> Continue : source/MIME mismatch or empty

  ProvideGuestData : IHostClipboard::ProvideData(requestId, Copy, Guest, mime, bytes)
  ProvideGuestData --> Continue : success or warning only

  OtherEvent : Handled by another focused diagram
  OtherEvent --> Continue

  Continue --> Waiting
  FailedEvent : Print serve failure
  FailedEvent --> Stopping
}

ServeLoop --> Cleanup : stopped
Failed --> Cleanup
Cleanup : IHostClipboard::Clear()
Cleanup : Unregister listener
Cleanup : Uninstall signal handler
Cleanup --> [*]

note right of DataRequestedEvent
  The event comes from Main's native lazy-render path.
  A host application requests an advertised guest format;
  Main registers a one-shot pending request and emits
  OnClipboardDataRequested with the request ID.
end note

note right of ProvideGuestData
  Main ProvideData path:
  - validates the pending request ID
  - matches action, source and format
  - consumes the request ID
  - stores matching guest-owned data
  - fires OnClipboardDataChanged after unlocking

  If the request became stale or no matching data is read,
  serve logs a warning and keeps running.
end note

@enduml
' EOF
